  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is to observe whether dexmedetomidine could reduce agitation during emergence from
      general anesthesia in patients undergoing retroperitoneal laparoscopic surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Agitation during emergence is frequent after retroperitoneal urologic surgery.
      Dexmedetomidine is alpha-2 receptor agonist which shows sedative and algesic effect. In this
      study we will compare the effect of dexmedetomidine given by different protocols on emergence
      agitation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
